All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Athlete
Represents the athletes that make up a Team.
AthleteContainer
Graphical element that creates and holds multiple AthletePanels.
AthletePanel
Graphical element that represents an Athlete as a panel which displays information about the athlete.
Buyable
Superclass for Athlete and Item.
Club
GUI for of viewing and organizing the Players' Athletes into different positions for the matches.
GenerateStats
Used for the random generation of various values used throughout the game.
Hub
GUI that acts as central hub of the game, displaying important information and used to access other GUIs.
InvalidTeamException
Throws an exception if we attempt to start the game with less Athletes than required for a full Team.
Item
Represents an item and that can be purchased by the Player at the Market.
ItemContainer
Graphical element that creates and holds multiple ItemPanels.
ItemPanel
Graphical element that represents an Item as panels in the Market and Club.
Market
Generates and stores Athletes and Items available for sale to the Player.
MarketWindow
GUI for the Market class.
Match
A match that is available for the Player to compete in.
MatchPanel
Graphical element that represents a Match as a panel in the StadiumWindow.
MatchWindow
GUI for playing Matches.
Notification
A pop-up window that is created to notify the Player with important messages.
Player
Stores information about the player and key variables for the game.
RandomEvent
Determines the random events that may (or may not) occur during the course of the game.
SetupWindow
GUI used to set starting conditions for the game.
Stadium
Generates and stores Matches available to the Player.
StadiumWindow
GUI for the Stadium class that displays currently available Matches.
Team
Represents a team that consists of Athletes.
TitleScreen
The title screen for the game, contains the main method for this package.
